<h3>Many talented composers have given there contribution to piano music.
Some of them are:
</h3>
<ul>
<li><u>Frederic Francois Chopin
</u></li>
<img src="chopin.jpg"
height="180px"
width="150px">
<p>
Frederic Francois Chopin, born on 1st March,1810 as Fryderyk Franciszek Chopin, was a Polish composer and virtuoso pianist of the Romantic era who wrote primarily for the solo piano. 
</p>
<hr></hr>
<li><u>Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart</u> 
</li>
<img src="mozart.jpg"
height="190px"
width="140px">
<p>
Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, baptised as Johannes Chrysostomus Wolfgangus Theophilus Mozart,
 was a prolific and influential composer of the Classical era. Born in Salzburg on 27 January 1756, he showed prodigious ability from his earliest childhood.
</p>
<hr></hr>
<li><u>Ludwig van Beethoven</u></li>
<img src="beethoven.jpeg"
height="180px"
width="150px">
<p>
Ludwig van Beethoven was a German composer and pianist born on December 1770.
 A crucial figure in the transition between the Classical 
 and Romantic eras in Western art music, he remains one of
 the most famous and influential of all composers. 
</p>
<hr></hr>
<li><u>Franz Liszt</u></li>
<img src="Liszt.jpg"
height="180px"
width="150px">
<p>
Franz Liszt was a prolific 19th-century Hungarian composer, virtuoso pianist, 
conductor, music teacher, arranger, organist, philanthropist, author, nationalist and a Franciscan tertiary.
He was born on  22 October 1811 in Raiding, Austria
</p>
<hr></hr>
<li><u>Johann Sebastian Bach </u></li>
<img src="bach.jpg"
height="180px"
width="150px">
<p>
Johann Sebastian Bach (31 March [O.S. 21 March] 1685 – 28 July 1750) was a German composer and musician 
of the Baroque period. He enriched established German styles through his mastery
 of counterpoint, harmonic and motivic organisation, and his adaptation of rhythms, 
 forms, and textures from abroad, particularly from Italy and France.
</p>
<hr></hr>
<li><u>George Frideric Handel</u> <li>
<img src="handel.jpg"
height="180px"
width="150px">
<p>
Georg Friedrich Handel, spelled in English George Frideric Handel was a German,
later British, baroque composer who spent the bulk of his career in London,
becoming well known for his operas, oratorios, anthems, and organ concertos. 
He was born on 23 February 1685 in Halle, Germany.
<p>
<hr></hr>
</ul>
<i>“Life is like a piano. What you get out of it depends on how you play it.” -Tom Lehrer</i>
